SOAPDeserializer
public class SectionVDeserializer
extends LiteralDeserializer
implements SOAPDeserializer

Converts into Java objects,the parameters in a SOAP payload that are encoded using the rules specified in SOAP 1.1 Section V. A SOAP payload created using Section V rules is popularly refered to as encoded using Section V encoding.

Method Detail

deserialize

public void deserialize()
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        WSDLException,
                        SOAPException
Reads the SOAP payload and converts any parameters into Java objects. If the payload encapsulates a <SOAP Fault>, it is converted into a Fault object.

The converted parameters are stored in the Envelope passed in the constructor.

The deserializer is able to process payload containing #href.

Specified by:
deserialize in interface SOAPDeserializer
Overrides:
deserialize in class LiteralDeserializer
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if any error occurs while reading the payload using the parser.
WSDLException - if any error occurs while reading the WSDL that contains the definition of the payload.
SOAPException - if any error occurs while processing the input SOAP payload.
